==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea coal
<hw>Sea" coal`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Coal brought by sea; -- a name by
which mineral coal was formerly designated in the south of England, in
distinction from <xex>charcoal</xex>, which was brought by
land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sea-coal facing</b></col> <fld>(Founding)</fld>,
<cd>facing consisting of pulverized bituminous coal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seacoast</ent>⟦br⟧
